Here, we will determine the awaiting time (AwaitingTime) which will be AppointmentDay - ScheduledDay, however, there are few issues with the dataset to begin with, let's explore that.

In [19]:
df['ScheduledDay'] = pd.to_datetime(df['ScheduledDay'], #turning string to pandas datetime
 format = '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ', 
 errors = 'coerce')
df['AppointmentDay'] = pd.to_datetime(df['AppointmentDay'], 
 format = '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ', 
 errors = 'coerce')

We are going to see that few values of scheduled is greater than Appoinment day

In [20]:
(df['ScheduledDay'] > df['AppointmentDay']).sum()
Out[20]:
38568

There are almost 40 thousand rows with Scheduled values greater than Appointment Day. This is because sometimes the appointment are made at the same day, and as time is not mentioned in AppointmentDay therefore, the values comes larger in Scheduled Day. To resolve this we will set AppointmentDay time to maximum and minus that by ScheduledDay.

In [21]:
df['AppointmentDay'] = df['AppointmentDay'] + pd.Timedelta('1d') - pd.Timedelta('1s')
In [22]:
(df['ScheduledDay'] > df['AppointmentDay']).sum()
Out[22]:
5

As most of the negative values are taken out for AwaitingTime, we can see only 5 values exist, these can be regarded as outliers or mistakes in the datasets. Therefore, its best to remove them.

In [44]:
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve
from sklearn.metrics import auc

fpr, tpr, threshold = roc_curve(y_test, nb_pred)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)

# method I: plt
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic')
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, 'b', label = 'AUC = %0.2f' % roc_auc)
plt.legend(loc = 'lower right')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1],'r--')
plt.xlim([0, 1])
plt.ylim([0, 1])
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.show()

If we see in the ROC curve, where the more the area the under the curve the better the model is performing, it is only 0.52, which is only 0.2 times greater than 0.5. Therefore, the area under the curve is not large and we can say that the model is not a relaible model. However, it can True negative values really well. This is the analysis of the Naive Bayes model.
